      "FacilityID": 40660,
      "SummaryText": "Indiana American Water Company's (IAW) Ogden Dunes Water Filtration Plant located in Portage, Indiana, utilizes chlorine for the purpose of disinfecting and treating potable, drinking water for the use by the surrounding communities.  The hazards associated with the chlorination process necessitates certain safety precautions associated with the receipt, storage, handling and use of this chemical.  precautions are taken to prevent unnecessary human exposure, to reduce the threat to employees, and ultimatley to reduce the threat of exposure to nearby members of the community.  A new dry system scrubber has been installed to mitigate/eliminate the potential of a chemical release into the atmosphere, and to the public.  A combination of a.) proper handling and storage, b.) modern safety designs of euqipment and the process, c.) mitigation control via an active dry scrubber system and d.) sufficient training of all appropriate personnel contribute to the overall goal of zero accidents and exposure incidents.\n\n\n"
